00:33:18.025 --> 00:33:22.340
the developed world, big,
massive conglomerate farms

00:33:22.340 --> 00:33:25.950
versus really what we're talking
about for the rest of

00:33:25.950 --> 00:33:29.860
the world, but also for us,
to buy local, small farms.

00:33:29.860 --> 00:33:32.072
There's a big kind of---

00:33:32.072 --> 00:33:32.900
I don't know.

00:33:32.900 --> 00:33:36.750
It's just a rub there, between
big business and really

00:33:36.750 --> 00:33:40.220
probably what's maybe the better
thing for all of us.

00:33:40.220 --> 00:33:42.620
Tell us where Oxfam stands
on those things.

00:33:42.620 --> 00:33:44.270
RAYMOND OFFENHEISER: Well, let
me, since this is a room of

00:33:44.270 --> 00:33:47.060
systems thinkers, I was told
