of international agriculture

00:43:43.410 --> 00:43:45.120
and food program that
he's been trying

00:43:45.120 --> 00:43:45.840
to get through Congress.

00:43:45.840 --> 00:43:46.920
There's been a lot
of resistance.

00:43:46.920 --> 00:43:47.950
And what is it about?

00:43:47.950 --> 00:43:50.960
It's about funding for small
farmer agriculture.

00:43:50.960 --> 00:43:53.260
It's about sustaining our
food aid program.

00:43:53.260 --> 00:43:55.800
United States has the largest
food aid program in the world.

00:43:55.800 --> 00:43:58.080
We provide 50% of the food
aid to emergency

00:43:58.080 --> 00:43:59.830
situations around the world.

00:43:59.830 --> 00:44:02.210
It's about increasing sort
of entrepreneurship and

00:44:02.210 --> 00:44:04.480
investment in entrepreneurship
of the sort

00:44:04.480 --> 00:44:05.910
that Susan's doing.

00:44:05.910 --> 00:44:06.800
Really important program.

00:44:06.800 --> 00:44:09.370
Something that you could
actually encourage your

00:44:09.370 --> 00:44:12.120
congressmen in this district,
or your districts in this

00:44:12.120 --> 00:44:15.050
general area, to actually
get behind.

00:44:15.050 --> 00:44:16.940
And we were challenging them
on the ethanol question.

00:44:16.940 --> 00:44:19.830
And we were challenging them
to take the climate change

00:44:19.830 --> 00:44:23.820
challenge real, to see it as a
real challenge that needed to

00:44:23.820 --> 00:44:24.690
be confronted.

00:44:24.690 --> 00:44:27.060
And we were encouraging them to
think about getting ahead

00:44:27.060 --> 00:44:29.860
of the climate change issue by
addressing the question of

00:44:29.860 --> 00:44:31.980
whether we need to be investing
in adaptation,

00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:35.430
helping some of these contexts
to actually adjust their

00:44:35.430 --> 00:44:38.070
farming systems to deal with
the challenges of climate

00:44:38.070 --> 00:44:40.270
change, to deal with resilience
and adaptation,

00:44:40.270 --> 00:44:43.100
which is sort of the front end
of dealing with climate change

00:44:43.100 --> 00:44:45.710
in the short to medium term.

00:44:45.710 --> 00:44:47.790
DIANE SOLINGER: Well, and we've
